00:50:52.316 --> 00:50:56.096 A:middle
So what I can do is right from
within the Photos app, tap Edit,

00:50:56.676 --> 00:51:00.106 A:middle
select the top left
extension button,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:50:56.676 --> 00:51:00.106 A:middle
select the top left
extension button,

00:51:00.536 --> 00:51:02.446 A:middle
and here you see our
sample extension.

00:51:02.716 --> 00:51:04.326 A:middle
So let me select it.

00:51:05.276 --> 00:51:08.336 A:middle
And what I can do is not
only apply our filters

00:51:08.336 --> 00:51:10.966 A:middle
but I can also resume what
was previously edited.

00:51:11.476 --> 00:51:14.056 A:middle
So, for example, I could decide
here to bring back the colors

00:51:14.316 --> 00:51:15.856 A:middle
and even enhance them.

00:51:15.996 --> 00:51:17.776 A:middle
So I'm going to replace
the Sepia filter

00:51:17.776 --> 00:51:19.906 A:middle
that was previously
applied and I'm going

00:51:19.906 --> 00:51:21.756 A:middle
to choose a Chrome filter.

00:51:23.116 --> 00:51:25.226 A:middle
And that's it.

00:51:26.306 --> 00:51:29.376 A:middle
You see how easy it is for
the user in just a few taps

00:51:29.906 --> 00:51:32.386 A:middle
to use your photo
editing extension.

00:51:38.136 --> 00:51:40.496 A:middle
So time to wrap up this session.

00:51:41.376 --> 00:51:42.226 A:middle
What have we learned?

00:51:42.466 --> 00:51:45.806 A:middle
We've introduced the new Photos
framework which allows you

00:51:45.806 --> 00:51:49.936 A:middle
to access the user's
photo library

00:51:50.186 --> 00:51:51.826 A:middle
and which allows
your application

00:51:52.836 --> 00:51:56.726 A:middle
to gain all the features like
the one which we provided

00:51:56.726 --> 00:51:57.926 A:middle
with the Photos application.

00:51:58.506 --> 00:52:02.086 A:middle
So your app can be a
first-class citizen


WEBVTT
